00365 class SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES
00366 {
00367   public:
00368     friend class SecurityHelper;    
00370     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() 
00371     {
00372         nSrtpKeyLength = 0 ;
00373         nSmimeKeyLength = 0 ;
00374         nSrtpLevel = SRTP_LEVEL_NONE ;
00375         memset(szSrtpKey, 0, sizeof(szSrtpKey));
00376         memset(szSmimeKeyDer, 0, sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer));
00377         memset(dbLocation, 0, sizeof(dbLocation));
00378         memset(szMyCertNickname, 0, sizeof(szMyCertNickname));
00379         memset(szCertDbPassword, 0, sizeof(szCertDbPassword));
00380     }    
00382     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00383     {
00384         copyData(ref);
00385     }    
00387     virtual ~SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() { }    
00389     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& operator=(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00390     {
00391         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00392         copyData(ref);
00393         return *this;
00394     }    
00399     void setSrtpKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00400     {
00401         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey);
00402         memcpy(szSrtpKey, szKey, safeLen);
00403         nSrtpKeyLength = safeLen;
00404     }    
00409     void setSmimeKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00410     {
00411         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer);
00412         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, szKey, safeLen);
00413         nSmimeKeyLength = safeLen;
00414     }
00418     void setSecurityLevel(SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL security) { nSrtpLevel = security; }
00422     const char* getSrtpKey() const  { return szSrtpKey; }    
00427     const char* getSmimeKey() const { return szSmimeKeyDer; }
00431     const int getSrtpKeyLength() const  { return nSrtpKeyLength; }
00436     const int getSmimeKeyLength() const { return nSmimeKeyLength; }
00440     const int getSecurityLevel() const {return nSrtpLevel;}
00446     const char* getCertDbLocation() const { return dbLocation; }
00447   private:
00448     SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL nSrtpLevel;
00449     char szSrtpKey[MAX_SRTP_KEY_LENGTH];
00450     int  nSrtpKeyLength;    
00451     char szSmimeKeyDer[MAX_SMIME_KEY_LENGTH];
00452     int  nSmimeKeyLength; 
00453     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00454     char dbLocation[256];                         
00455     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00456     char szMyCertNickname[32];   
00457     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00458     char szCertDbPassword[MAX_PASSWORD_LENGTH];   
00459     void copyData(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00460     {
00461         nSrtpLevel = ref.nSrtpLevel;
00462         nSrtpKeyLength = ref.nSrtpKeyLength;
00463         nSmimeKeyLength = ref.nSmimeKeyLength;
00464         memcpy(szSrtpKey, ref.szSrtpKey, ref.nSrtpKeyLength);
00465         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, ref.szSmimeKeyDer, ref.nSmimeKeyLength);
00466         strncpy(dbLocation, ref.dbLocation, sizeof(dbLocation) - 1);
00467         strncpy(szMyCertNickname, ref.szMyCertNickname, sizeof(szMyCertNickname) - 1);
00468         strncpy(szCertDbPassword, ref.szCertDbPassword, sizeof(szCertDbPassword) - 1);
00469     }
00470 };

00527         type = SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE_TYPE;
00528         handle = NULL;

00531     ~SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00532     {
00533         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00534         {
00535 #ifdef      _WIN32
00536             if (handle) ((IUnknown*)handle)->Release();
00537 #endif              
00538         }
00539     }
00541     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00542     {
00543         copy(ref);
00544     }
00546     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& operator=(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00547     {
00548         // check for assignment to self
00549         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00550         copy(ref);
00551         return *this;
00552     }    
00553     int cbSize;                     
00554     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY_TYPE type;   
00555     union
00556     {
00557         SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE handle;  
00558         IBaseFilter* filter;        
00559     };
00560 private:
00561     void copy(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00562     {
00563         cbSize = ref.cbSize;
00564         type = ref.type;
00565         handle = ref.handle;
00566         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00567         {
00568 #ifdef      _WIN32
00569             // we should addRef here.
00570             if (handle) ((IBaseFilter*)handle)->AddRef();
00571 #endif            
00572         }
00573     }
00574     
00575 };

00589 struct SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS
00590 {
00592     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS()
00593     {
00594         cbSize = sizeof(SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS);
00595         memset((void*)cInterface, 0, sizeof(cInterface));
00596         memset((void*)cIpAddress, 0, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00597         memset((void*)cCustomTransportName, 0, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00598         memset((void*)cCustomRouteID, 0, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00599         eContactType = CONTACT_AUTO;
00600         eTransportType = TRANSPORT_UDP ;
00601         id = 0;
00602         iPort = -1;
00603     }
00605     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00606     {
00607         cbSize = sizeof(SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS);
00608         strncpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface, sizeof(cInterface));
00609         strncpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00610         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00611         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00612         id = ref.id;
00613         iPort = ref.iPort;
00614         if (ref.cbSize == sizeof(SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS))
00615         {
00616         strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, 32);
00617         strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00618     }
00619         else
00620         {
00621             memset((void*)cCustomTransportName, 0, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00622             memset((void*)cCustomRouteID, 0, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00623         }
00624     }
00625 
00627     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& operator=(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00628     {
00629         // check for assignment to self
00630         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00631         strncpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface, sizeof(cInterface));
00632         strncpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00633         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00634         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00635         id = ref.id;
00636         iPort = ref.iPort;
00637         if (cbSize == sizeof(SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS))
00638         {
00639             strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00640             strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00641         }
00642         return *this;
00643     }    
00644     SIPX_CONTACT_ID     id;              
00645     SIPX_CONTACT_TYPE   eContactType ;   
00646     SIPX_TRANSPORT_TYPE eTransportType ; 
00647     char                cInterface[32] ; 
00648     char                cIpAddress[28] ; 
00649     int                 cbSize;      
00650     int                 iPort ;          
00651     char                cCustomTransportName[32]; 
00652     char                cCustomRouteID[64] ; 
00654 /*
00655     NOTE: I've carved a cbSize out of the cIpAddress to allow binary backwards 
00656           compatibilty with older version of the DLL.  If the cbSize isn't 
00657           want we expected, we should not touch data members.
00658 */
00659 };
